Varaiables and Methods:
------------------------
Variable: 
    its a box that stores data.

     Syntax -
         datatype name = value;
datatype - this defines which type of data we are keeping in the memory.
name - reference to the data in the memory
value - actual data.


ex: int age = 25;
    String name = "Akshay is ugly guy";
    double salary = 5000.00; 

Types of variables:
----------------------
local variables:
   created and used inside the method.
Instance variables: 
    Created inside a class and outside method. Each object gets its own copy.
static variables: 
    Belongs to class, shared by all objects.

Methods:
---------
    A block of code that can perform some work.
    Method is used to (perform an action) or (perform task/action and return a result) 
  Syntax: 
       returnType methodName(parameters){
         //code
       }

      No return No param
      ----------------------
      ex: void greet(){
         
            System.out.println(Hello");
      }     

      method with paramamters:
      ----------------------------------
         void printName(String name){
            Syste.out.println("My Name is :"+name);
         }
         
         object.printName("Akash");

      method with multiple paramamters and return type :
      --------------------------------------------------------
         int doAdd(int a, int b, int c){
            int d = a + b + c;
            return d;
         }

         int result = doAdd(10, 20, 30);
         sop("result: "+ result);

      ----------------------------------------------------------
      Write 3 classes:
      class VoidNoParamDemo{
         void greet(){
         
            System.out.println(Hello");
      }   

      psvm(){
         VoidNoParamDemo voidNoParamDemo = new VoidNoParamDemo();
         voidNoParamDemo.greet();

